The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Losses mount at Birla firm
                                                                                                               Losses mount at Birla firm
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Mumbai, April 28: Aditya Birla Nuvos net loss for the quarter ended March 31, 2009 has widened to Rs 141.15 crore from Rs 21.84 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year.        
	The companys total income rose to Rs 4,275.26 crore during the period from Rs 2,937 crore a year ago.         
	The annual results of the company also show a sharp drop in earnings. On a consolidated basis, Aditya Birla Nuvo suffered a net loss of Rs 430.5 crore for the year ended March 31, 2009 against a net profit of Rs 150.78 crore last year. Total income increased to Rs 13,810.48 crore from Rs 11,935.40 crore.        
	Garments and carbon black were worst hit in 2008-09. Garments suffered a loss of Rs 48.54 crore against a profit of Rs 35.08 crore last year, while the profit before interest and tax for carbon black declined to Rs 24.69 crore from Rs 130.32 crore a year ago.         
	In a separate filing with the BSE, the company said its chief financial officer and whole-time director Adesh Gupta had resigned with effect from May 1, 2009. Sushil Agarwal will take over as the CFO.         
	Rakesh Jain has been appointed as the managing director with effect from July 1, 2009. Pranab Barua will be a whole-time director and Santrupt Mishra will head the carbon black business from May 1.         
	The board of directors proposed a dividend of Rs 4 (on shares of face value of Rs 10 each) at its meeting held today.                                                                                                                                       
